n|United States}} [[2002 FIBA World Championship|2002]]\n|Sixth place\n|6th of 16\n|9\n|6\n|3\n|832\n|679\n| +153\n|[[George Karl|Karl]]\n|- style=\"background:#cc9966\"\n|{{flagicon|Japan}} [[2006 FIBA World Championship|2006]]\n|'''Third place'''\n|'''3rd of 24'''\n|'''9'''\n|'''8'''\n|'''1'''\n|'''932'''\n|'''748'''\n|'''+184'''\n|Krzyzewski\n|- style=\"background:gold\"\n|{{flagicon|Turkey}} [[2010 FIBA World Championship|2010]]\n|'''[[2010 FIBA World Championship Final|Champions]]'''\n|'''1st of 24'''\n|'''9'''\n|'''9'''\n|'''0'''\n|'''835'''\n|'''614'''\n|'''+221'''\n|rowspan=2|Krzyzewski\n|- style=\"background:gold\"\n|{{flagicon|Spain}} [[2014 FIBA Basketball World Cup|2014]]\n|'''[[2014 FIBA Basketball World Cup Final|Champions]]'''\n|'''1st of 24'''\n|'''9'''\n|'''9'''\n|'''0'''\n|'''941'''\n|'''644'''\n|'''+297'''\n|-\n|{{flagicon|China}} [[2019 FIBA Basketball World Cup|2019]]\n|Seventh place\n|7th of 32\n|'''9'''\n|'''6'''\n|'''2'''\n|'''692'''\n|'''587'''\n|'''+105'''\n|[[Gregg Popovich|Popovich]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Philippines}}{{flagicon|Japan}}{{flagicon|Indonesia}} [[2023 FIBA Basketball World Cup|2023]]\n|colspan=8|''To be determined''\n|\n|-\n|'''Total'''\n|'''5 titles'''\n|'''18/19'''\n|'''158'''\n|'''129'''\n|'''29'''\n|'''13929'''\n|'''11354'''\n|'''+1883'''\n|\n|}\n\n====FIBA AmeriCup====\nPrior to the implementation of a new FIBA competition system in 2017, the U.S. team used different players depending on the circumstances. In 1992,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usab.com/history/national-team-mens/mens-tournament-of-the-americas-1992.aspx|title=MEN'S TOURNAMENT OF THE AMERICAS -- 1992|publisher=USA Basketball}}</ref> 1999,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usab.com/history/national-team-mens/mens-tournament-of-the-americas-1999.aspx|title=MEN'S TOURNAMENT OF THE AMERICAS -- 1999|publisher=USA Basketball}}</ref> 2003<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usab.com/history/national-team-mens/mens-tournament-of-the-americas-2003.aspx|title=MEN'S TOURNAMENT OF THE AMERICAS -- 2003|publisher=USA Basketball}}</ref> and 2007,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usab.com/history/national-team-mens/mens-fiba-americas-championship-2007.aspx|title=MEN'S FIBA AMERICAS CHAMPIONSHIP 2007|publisher=USA Basketball}}</ref> the Americans sent in NBA players as they needed to qualify for the Olympics. In 1989<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usab.com/history/national-team-mens/fiba-americas-championship-1989.aspx|title=FIBA Americas Championship -- 1989|publisher=USA Basketball}}</ref> and 2005,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usab.com/history/national-team-mens/fiba-americas-championship-2005.aspx|title=FIBA Americas Championship -- 2005|publisher=USA Basketball}}</ref> the U.S. also used the tournament for qualification purposes but sent in either college players (in 1989 NBA players weren't allowed) or [[NBA G League|NBA Development League]], [[Continental Basketball Association|CBA]] and European leagues players (in 2005 the U.S. team didn't need to win gold in order to qualify for the World Championship). In 1993,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usab.com/history/national-team-mens/fiba-americas-championship-1993.aspx|title=FIBA Americas Championship -- 1993|publisher=USA Basketball}}</ref> 1997<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usab.com/history/national-team-mens/fiba-americas-championship-1997.aspx|title=FIBA Americas Championship -- 1997|publisher=USA Basketball}}</ref> and 2001,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usab.com/history/national-team-mens/fiba-americas-championship-2001.aspx|title=FIBA Americas Championship -- 2001|publisher=USA Basketball}}</ref> the U.S. team entered the tournament without any specific purpose and was represented by CBA players in 1993 and 1997, and by [[National Junior College Athletic Association|junior players]] in 2001. In 1980, 1984, 1988, 1995, 2009, 2011, 2013 and 2015, the American team didn't enter the tournament. In 2017,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usab.com/history/national-team-mens/fiba-americas-championship-2017.aspx|title=FIBA AmeriCup -- 2017|publisher=USA Basketball}}</ref> the U.S. participated for the first time in ten years with a squad of NBA G League players and American professionals playing in European leagues.\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!colspan=9|[[FIBA AmeriCup|FIBA AmeriCup record]]\n!rowspan=2|Manager(s)\n|-\n!Year\n!Round\n!Position\n!{{Tooltip|Pld|Games played}}\n!{{Tooltip|W|Won}}\n!{{Tooltip|L|Lost}}\n!{{Tooltip|PF|Points for}}\n!{{Tooltip|PA|Points against}}\n!{{Tooltip|PD|Points difference}}\n|- \n|{{flagicon|Puerto Rico|1952}} [[1980 Tournament of the Americas|1980]]\n|rowspan=3 colspan=8|''Did not participate''\n|\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Brazil|1968}} [[1984 Tournament of the Americas|1984]]\n|\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Uruguay}} [[1988 Tournament of the Americas|1988]]\n|\n|- style=\"background:silver\"\n|{{flagicon|Mexico}} [[1989 Tournament of the Americas|1989]]\n|'''Runners-up'''\n|'''2nd of 12'''\n|'''8'''\n|'''6'''\n|'''2'''\n|'''776'''\n|'''740'''\n|'''+36'''\n|[[Bobby Cremins|Cremins]]\n|- style=\"background:gold\"\n|style=\"border: 3px solid red\"|{{flagicon|United States}} [[1992 Tournament of the Americas|1992]]\n|'''Champions'''\n|'''1st of 10'''\n|'''6'''\n|'''6'''\n|'''0'''\n|'''727'''\n|'''418'''\n|'''+309'''\n|[[Chuck Daly|Daly]]\n|- style=\"background:gold\"\n|{{flagicon|Puerto Rico|1952}} [[1993 Tournament of the Americas|1993]]\n|'''Champions'''\n|'''1st of 10'''\n|'''7'''\n|'''6'''\n|'''1'''\n|'''710'''\n|'''659'''\n|'''+51'''\n|[[Mike Thibault|Thibault]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Argentina}} [[1995 Tournament of the Americas|1995]]\n|colspan=8|''Did not participate''\n|\n|- style=\"background:gold\"\n|{{flagicon|Uruguay}} [[1997 Tournament of the Americas|1997]]\n|'''Champions'''\n|'''1st of 10'''\n|'''9'''\n|'''8'''\n|'''1'''\n|'''845'''\n|'''759'''\n|'''+86'''\n|[[Morris McHone|McHone]]\n|- style=\"background:gold\"\n|{{flagicon|Puerto Rico}} [[1999 Tournament of the Americas|1999]]\n|'''Champions'''\n