{"title_page": "Paul Seitz (footballer)", "text_new": "{{short description|French footballer}}\n{{One source|date=October 2010}}\n'''Paul Seitz''' (15 July 1897 \u2013 22 February 1979) was a [[France|French]] footballer.\n\nHe spent his entire career as a footballer at [[Olympique de Marseille]] (from 1919 to 1926) and took the club to two [[Coupe de France|Coupes de Frances]] (in 1924 as a [[defender (football)|defender]] and in 1926 as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]]). In 1921, he refused to play for the [[France national football team]]. He was also coach of the phoc\u00e9en club in 1942.\n\n== Sources ==\n{{cite book\n  |editor=L'\u00c9quipe\n  |title=Coupe de France : La folle \u00e9pop\u00e9e\n  |authors=Collectif\n  |language=fr\n  |year=2007\n  |isbn=2-915535-62-0\n}}\n\n{{Olympique de Marseille managers}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2010}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Seitz, Paul}}\n[[Category:1897 births]]\n[[Category:1979 deaths]]\n[[Category:French footballers]]\n[[Category:French football managers]]\n[[Category:Olympique de Marseille players]]\n[[Category:Olympique de Marseille managers]]\n\n\n{{France-footy-defender-1890s-stub}}\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n", "text_old": "{{One source|date=October 2010}}\n'''Paul Seitz''' (15 July 1897 \u2013 22 February 1979) was a [[France|French]] footballer.\n\nHe spent his entire career as a footballer at [[Olympique de Marseille]] (from 1919 to 1926) and took the club to two [[Coupe de France|Coupes de Frances]] (in 1924 as a [[defender (football)|defender]] and in 1926 as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]]). In 1921, he refused to play for the [[France national football team]]. He was also coach of the phoc\u00e9en club in 1942.\n\n== Sources ==\n{{cite book\n  |editor=L'\u00c9quipe\n  |title=Coupe de France : La folle \u00e9pop\u00e9e\n  |authors=Collectif\n  |language=fr\n  |year=2007\n  |isbn=2-915535-62-0\n}}\n\n{{Olympique de Marseille managers}}\n{{Use dmy dates